<div class="l-content-large -breastfeeding">
  <div class="row reorder">
    <div class="columns small-12 medium-5">
      <div class="c-graphic -breastfeeding">
        <img src="<%= asset_path('illustrations/04_01_Breastfeeding_Woman&Child.png') %>"/>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="columns small-12 medium-7 text">
      <div class="c-cta">
        <h1 class="text -cta-title">Exclusive breastfeeding</h1>
        <p class="text -cta-text">Exclusive breastfeeding — defined as the practice of only giving an infant breast-milk for the 6 months of life — is a cornerstone of child survival and child health. It boosts a child’s immune system, protects against diseases, increases intelligence, and promotes healthy growth. With the potential to save as many as 823,000 lives per year, exclusive breastfeeding has the single largest potential impact on child survival of any preventive intervention.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="columns small-12 accordion">
      <div class="c-accordion">
        <input id="ac-breastfeeding" name="accordion-breastfeeding" type="checkbox" />
        <label class="text -accordion -open columns small-12 medium-7 medium-offset-5" for="ac-breastfeeding">See why it matters</label>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <div class="columns small-12 medium-7">
            <div class="c-cta">
